snippet.title: "Look At The Barnet and The Teeth" Lewis-Skelly’s Prank Call, Ultimate 5-A-Side & Dan Burn’s Height!
snippet.description:
From breakfast habits to first football memories, surprise call-ups, and the best (and worst) future England managers – this episode of England Generations is packed with laughs, banter, and behind-the-scenes stories.

Declan Rice, Dan Burn, and Myles Lewis-Skelly sit down to chat about their journeys to the national team, including the unexpected ways they found out about their England call-ups. Dan recalls his wild rise from grassroots football to the Premier League, while Myles shares what it’s like breaking through at such a young age. Declan, as always, keeps the energy high – whether it’s revealing team nicknames (spoiler: "Horseman" is involved) or debating the ultimate England five-a-side team.

Plus, check out meta updates with new Skirmisher perks and Alter ability updates.

Learn more: http://x.ea.com/apxl/beast-mode-event

snippet.title: NASA’s SpaceX Crew-9 Re-Entry and Splashdown
snippet.description:
Watch with us as the four members of NASA's SpaceX Crew-9 mission—NASA astronauts Nick Hague, Suni Williams, Butch Wilmore, and cosmonaut Aleksandr Gorbunov—return to Earth.

Suni Williams and Butch Wilmore began their mission at the International Space Station on June 6, 2024, arriving aboard Boeing's Starliner spacecraft. Nick Hague and Aleksandr Gorbunov arrived at the station on Sept. 29, 2024. Hague and Gorbunov launched to space aboard SpaceX's Dragon Freedom spacecraft, which was docked to the station since its arrival in September, and has since brought Crew-9 back home.

2:24 Return coverage begins
6:41 Meet the crew
28:14 Deorbit burn start
1:05:20 First views from WB-57 aircraft
1:09:37 Drogue chutes deploy
1:10:31 Main chutes deploy
1:12:00 Splashdown
1:33:56 Dolphins
1:38:33 Hoist
1:53:45 Hatch open
1:57:09 Crew egress

See the full schedule for Crew-9's return to Earth: https://go.nasa.gov/4iWeg8N
Learn more about Crew-9's scientific mission: https://go.nasa.gov/4bWdt5u
Follow the latest Crew-9 mission updates: https://www.nasa.gov/blogs/commercialcrew

Credit: NASA
